com.att.research.xacmlatt.pdp.std.functions

Class FunctionDefinitionBase<O,I>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.att.research.xacmlatt.pdp.std.functions.FunctionDefinitionBase<O,I>
  • Type Parameters:
    O - the java class for the Output data type returned by the FunctionDefinition
    I - the java class for the Input data type expected in the arguments to the FunctionDefinition. Some functions have non-homogeneous arguments but may still have a main 'type'.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    FunctionDefinition
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FunctionDefinitionAccessPermitted, FunctionDefinitionBag, FunctionDefinitionBagIsIn, FunctionDefinitionBagOneAndOnly, FunctionDefinitionBagSize, FunctionDefinitionDateTimeArithmetic, FunctionDefinitionHigherOrderBag, FunctionDefinitionHomogeneousSimple, FunctionDefinitionRegexpMatch, FunctionDefinitionRFC822NameMatch, FunctionDefinitionSet, FunctionDefinitionStringFunctions, FunctionDefinitionURIStringConcatenate

    public abstract class FunctionDefinitionBase<O,I>
extends java.lang.Object
implements FunctionDefinition
    /** FunctionDefinitionBase provides a common base for FunctionDefinitions. The child classes derived from this are of two types:
    • Functions returning a single simple value of a type defined in DataTypes. These functions will all derive from com.att.research.xacmlatt.pdp.std.functions.FunctionDefinitionSimple.
    • Functions returning a single bag with elements of a single type.

        This base class contains the following components:

        • The Identity for this function.
        • The DataType of the data returned from this function. For Bags this means the DataType of the elements in the bag, or null if that is ambiguous.
        • Commonly-used values.
    Author:
    glenngriffin
